  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 7 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 17 high, 6 medium, 16 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT); plus 14 other bases. 6 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is fog / freezing fog, mist and very low visibility  — most notably around Warsaw Chopin (WAW/EPWA), Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ) and London Luton (LTN/EGGW). Network hotspots: Brindisi (BDS/LIBR), Marche (AOI/LIPY), Keflavik (KEF/BIKF), Mohammed V (CMN/GMMN), Glasgow (GLA/EGPF) and 2 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, RVR limitations and approach minima limits. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 4 airports changed status, led by Kaunas (KUN/EYKA), Alicante-Elche Miguel Hernández (ALC/LEAL), Turku (TKU/EFTU) and 1 others.",
